    840266,"High Tide (Part Two)", 729520,"Wolverine is in West Berlin and is being followed by the KGB. Wolverine avoids a confrontation with them but Charlie kills them allowing Wolverine to catch his smell. Wolverine walks past Peter Parker and identifies him as Spider-Man. He then tracks Spider-Man to his hotel and forces Peter to follow him even though he has no costume. He tells Peter to go back home. When Peter returns to the hotel he discovers that Ned is dead with his throat slit. Some armed agents ask him questions initially in German then Russian. Wolverine then busts through the window and deals with them. Spider-Man decides to stick around and gets a costume from a costume shop. He crosses the border into East Berlin. He tracks a tracer he tagged Wolverine with only to discover that Wolverine is one step ahead. Wolverine discovers Charlie who turns out to be a woman and she takes him back to her large house. Wolverine promises to protect her.",NULL,"The original story has been broken up into parts for release in various issues.",19);
